Create xlsx labeling file

Source: R/create_labelingFile.R
create_labelingFile.Rd

A function to create the xlsx file to do the labeling

Usage

create_labelingFile(
  crownsFile,
  site = NULL,
  dates = NULL,
  save_xlsx = FALSE,
  directory = NULL
)

Arguments

crownsFile

sf object. The crowns delineation file. It should include 'id', 'species', 'genus' and 'family' columns.

site

chr. site name.

dates

chr. vector of dates (format should be 'YYYY_MM_DD', p.e '20220925').

save_xlsx

logical. If TRUE, it will save the table as xlsx file. Indicate the path as the directory parameters

directory

The path where to save the xlsx file.

full.names = TRUE

'crowns/Bouamir_crowns.gpkg'
)
crownsFile <- sf::read_sf(path_crownsFile)

site = 'Bouamir'
dates <- paste(
str_sub(stringr::str_split(basename(rgb_paths), '_', simplify = TRUE)[,2],1,4),
str_sub(stringr::str_split(basename(rgb_paths), '_', simplify = TRUE)[,2],5,6),
str_sub(stringr::str_split(basename(rgb_paths), '_', simplify = TRUE)[,2],7,8),
sep = ''
)
